WEBVTT

00:11.489 --> 00:13.143
Good afternoon, Mr. LeRoux.

00:13.187 --> 00:15.798
I have 567 true-or-
false statements.

00:15.841 --> 00:18.409
I use my wife's e-mail account
to avoid detection.

00:18.453 --> 00:20.281
I said I want out!Oh, you're never
getting out.

00:20.324 --> 00:21.891
Three missing Hispanic youths.

00:21.934 --> 00:24.546
KRISTEN:
I think the husband did it. DAVID: Me, too.

00:24.589 --> 00:26.026
ANDY:
You miss it. You should take

00:26.069 --> 00:27.288
the tour of Everest
in the spring.

00:27.331 --> 00:28.593
My youngest daughter,

00:28.637 --> 00:30.987
Laura, she was born
with a heart defect.

00:31.031 --> 00:32.467
[shouting, grunting]

00:39.126 --> 00:42.390
MAN:
In America, men are so lucky.

00:42.433 --> 00:44.218
In my country...
[chuckles]

00:44.261 --> 00:46.698
you wake up, you are 22,

00:46.742 --> 00:49.092
you have 15 wives and 42 kids.

00:49.136 --> 00:50.485
[scattered laughter]

00:50.528 --> 00:52.748
But I am kidding.

00:52.791 --> 00:54.750
I only have 32 children.

00:54.793 --> 00:57.100
[scattered laughter]My ex-wife,

00:57.144 --> 00:59.494
she's always mad
about something, yeah?

00:59.537 --> 01:01.931
"Why did you give Joseph

01:01.974 --> 01:03.541
"the peanut butter sandwich?

01:03.585 --> 01:05.195
Now he has a rash."

01:05.239 --> 01:07.371
And all I can think is...

01:07.415 --> 01:09.243
"Who is Joseph?"

01:09.286 --> 01:12.072
[laughter]

01:12.115 --> 01:14.291
COMEDIAN:
♪ The baby's gonna
have himself ♪

01:14.335 --> 01:16.337
♪ A biscuit today.
Wait, what?!

01:16.380 --> 01:17.990
That's not how it goes.

01:18.034 --> 01:20.210
We're not barbarians.
Are you kidding me?

01:20.254 --> 01:21.385
I'll do it again.

01:21.429 --> 01:22.778
♪ Everybody's happy that...

01:22.821 --> 01:24.301
One more.You got it.

01:25.389 --> 01:26.869
Hi.

01:26.912 --> 01:29.219
I really enjoyed your set.

01:29.263 --> 01:31.047
Yeah?

01:31.091 --> 01:33.354
Are you an aspiring comedian?

01:33.397 --> 01:35.138
No accent.Yeah,

01:35.182 --> 01:37.184
it's, um,
part of my schtick on stage.

01:37.227 --> 01:38.402
Ah.Ah.

01:38.446 --> 01:40.578
What's your name?

01:40.622 --> 01:42.972
Sonia.

01:43.015 --> 01:44.582
[door closes]MAN:
I made you laugh.

01:44.626 --> 01:47.977
[laughing]Oh. This is a
nice apartment.

01:48.020 --> 01:50.066
Are you independently
wealthy?

01:50.110 --> 01:51.285
[laughs]:
No.

01:51.328 --> 01:53.461
I just, um...

01:53.504 --> 01:55.202
I invest well.

01:56.333 --> 01:58.292
I should give my money to you.

01:58.335 --> 01:59.684
How do you do it?

01:59.728 --> 02:01.382
I anticipate disasters.

02:01.425 --> 02:03.471
I sell short at bad times.

02:03.514 --> 02:05.212
Hmm.Some scotch?

02:05.255 --> 02:06.387
Sounds good.

02:06.430 --> 02:07.910
[thump]

02:11.392 --> 02:13.394
Sorry. Um...

02:13.437 --> 02:14.786
I only carry it

02:14.830 --> 02:17.311
because I've been jumped
a few times going home.

02:17.354 --> 02:19.313
I don't like guns.

02:19.356 --> 02:21.010
Neither do I.

02:21.053 --> 02:22.577
Y-You know what?
It'll be...

02:22.620 --> 02:25.275
far over here,

02:25.319 --> 02:26.450
right there,

02:26.494 --> 02:28.322
where you can see it.

02:28.365 --> 02:30.976
And I'll be over here,
where you can see me.

02:31.020 --> 02:32.543
[laughs]

02:34.545 --> 02:36.547
Do you ever bring back
your earlier jokes?

02:36.591 --> 02:38.549
My earlier jokes?Mm-hmm.

02:39.550 --> 02:41.291
Which ones?

02:41.335 --> 02:44.512
You used to do one
about dancing.

02:44.555 --> 02:47.732
Oh, wow, you've been
following me for a while.

02:47.776 --> 02:48.559
A long while.

02:48.603 --> 02:49.821
Oh, should I be worried?

02:49.865 --> 02:52.433
[laughs]:
Very.

02:52.476 --> 02:54.522
The earlier jokes. Hmm.

02:55.784 --> 02:57.220
Tell me one.

02:57.264 --> 02:58.526
Mm.

02:58.569 --> 03:01.442
[exhales]:
Ah...

03:01.485 --> 03:03.139
Hello, my friends.

03:03.183 --> 03:05.315
I want to teach you
a new dance.

03:05.359 --> 03:07.404
It's called
"Kill the cockroaches."

03:07.448 --> 03:09.406
Ah! There's
a mama cockroach.

03:09.450 --> 03:11.016
Cha-cha-cha.[taps foot]

03:11.060 --> 03:12.322
And father and brother.

03:12.366 --> 03:13.541
Cha-cha-cha.

03:13.584 --> 03:14.803
Oh, and don't forget
the babies,

03:14.846 --> 03:16.370
because they
will grow up to breed.

03:16.413 --> 03:18.937
[laughs]:
Cha-cha-cha.

03:20.939 --> 03:22.419
What's wrong?

03:23.464 --> 03:25.379
Who are you?

03:25.422 --> 03:28.033
Sonia.

03:28.077 --> 03:30.471
Wh...
Why, who are you?

03:32.690 --> 03:34.431
I'm gonna go.

03:34.475 --> 03:36.172
Sorry.
Thank you.

03:37.478 --> 03:39.088
[grunts]

03:44.659 --> 03:46.530
[phone vibrating]

03:47.575 --> 03:49.664
Oh! God.

03:49.707 --> 03:51.056
I'm here, I'm here, I'm here.

03:51.100 --> 03:52.884
I know, and I need you here.

03:52.928 --> 03:54.538
Yeah, well,
just give me 20 minutes.

03:54.582 --> 03:56.453
I'm just...
getting my files together.

03:56.497 --> 03:59.456
Okay, but...
just know this looks bad.

03:59.500 --> 04:00.892
LYNN:
They're never
gonna let LeRoux out.

04:00.936 --> 04:01.937
Hurry.

04:01.980 --> 04:03.373
Okay.

04:03.417 --> 04:06.507
[man chanting indistinctly
in distance]

