14:24.472 --> 14:27.214
I'm hurt.I'm so sorry.

14:29.085 --> 14:31.087
I can't.

14:31.131 --> 14:33.394
My friend Ben dropped me off.
He's coming back any minute.

14:33.437 --> 14:34.786
You have
to let us go, Sonia.

14:34.830 --> 14:37.093
[chiming]

14:37.137 --> 14:39.313
♪ All that she wants

14:39.356 --> 14:42.185
♪ Is another baby

14:42.229 --> 14:44.492
♪ Yeah...

14:44.535 --> 14:46.233
DISC JOCKEY:
That is "All That She Wants"

14:46.276 --> 14:50.411
from Ace of Base, number four
on the American hit charts.

14:50.454 --> 14:52.239
COMEDIAN: And a favorite
of our Hutu brothers.

14:52.282 --> 14:54.806
DISC JOCKEY:
But not our Tutsi brothers?

14:54.850 --> 14:57.200
COMEDIAN: To be my brother,
you must share a mother.

14:57.244 --> 14:58.419
And my mother was no cockroach.

14:58.462 --> 15:00.856
[laughter,
applause sound effect]

15:00.900 --> 15:02.292
DISC JOCKEY:
And what do you say

15:02.336 --> 15:04.991
to those who argue Tutsis
are just like us?

15:05.034 --> 15:07.341
Blood runs through their veins.COMEDIAN: So do cockroaches.

15:07.384 --> 15:09.169
But I'm not a cockroach.

15:09.212 --> 15:10.735
[squishing sound effect,
laughter]

15:10.779 --> 15:12.389
DISC JOCKEY:
Who was that?

15:12.433 --> 15:15.088
COMEDIAN: My neighbor.
Oops, here comes his wife.

15:15.131 --> 15:17.090
[squishing sound effect]

15:17.133 --> 15:19.222
[laughter]

15:19.266 --> 15:21.311
DISC JOCKEY: Now you've made
a mess of my floor.

15:21.355 --> 15:24.401
COMEDIAN: I think you have a
Tutsi intern to clean it up.

15:24.445 --> 15:26.490
Hey, Ngabo.[door opens]

15:26.534 --> 15:28.362
TUTSI INTERN:
Y-Yes, sir, what do you need?

15:28.405 --> 15:30.930
COMEDIAN:
Can you just clean up there?

15:30.973 --> 15:32.583
TUTSI INTERN:
Clean up what where?

15:32.627 --> 15:34.237
COMEDIAN:
You have to bend down.

15:34.281 --> 15:36.326
DISC JOCKEY: Oh, no.COMEDIAN: Get very close.

15:36.370 --> 15:37.806
See?TUTSI INTERN: Yes.

15:37.849 --> 15:39.373
I-I think it's...[squishing sound effect]

15:39.416 --> 15:41.462
[laughter]

15:41.505 --> 15:43.507
[beeps]

15:48.686 --> 15:50.558
[panting]

15:50.601 --> 15:52.429
That wasn't me.

15:52.473 --> 15:54.083
Yes, it was.I worked at the
radio station,

15:54.127 --> 15:55.302
but that, I never did that.

15:55.345 --> 15:56.564
April 4,

15:56.607 --> 15:58.392
1994.

15:58.435 --> 16:01.351
That was the broadcast
three days before it started.

16:01.395 --> 16:03.266
You can download it
from the...LANDO: I-I understand.

16:03.310 --> 16:05.007
But that wasn't me.Sonia.

16:05.051 --> 16:06.400
You called me

16:06.443 --> 16:08.010
because you wanted to talk.

16:08.054 --> 16:10.273
Let's talk.

16:10.317 --> 16:13.102
SONIA:
Radio Two encouraged

16:13.146 --> 16:17.106
the Hutu majority to take to the
streets to massacre the Tutsi.

16:17.150 --> 16:19.543
That man over there
is Jean Bakunda,

16:19.587 --> 16:22.503
the funnyman
of Radio Two.No, Sonia.

16:22.546 --> 16:26.333
I am Lando Mutabazi,
an immigrant

16:26.376 --> 16:27.377
from Rwanda.

16:27.421 --> 16:28.988
I suffered, too, just like you.

16:29.031 --> 16:31.729
I'm sorry. Did you want to talk
to me about how you suffer?

16:31.773 --> 16:33.035
Sonia.

16:33.079 --> 16:34.732
I am not who
you think I am.

16:34.776 --> 16:36.343
DAVID:
Don't! Sonia.

16:36.386 --> 16:37.518
Look at me.

16:37.561 --> 16:39.999
You said you
felt this thing,

16:40.042 --> 16:42.392
this evil oppressing you.

16:42.436 --> 16:44.177
Killing him is evil.

16:45.656 --> 16:48.659
He broadcast for the
next hundred days.

16:48.703 --> 16:49.965
Wasn't me.

16:50.009 --> 16:53.360
He encouraged the Hutus
to take to the streets,

16:53.403 --> 16:56.972
to break into homes, churches,
raping Tutsi women,

16:57.016 --> 16:58.887
hacking innocent people.

16:58.930 --> 17:02.195
With machetes exactly like this.I did not...

17:02.238 --> 17:05.024
I did not. I swear.
I'm just a comedian.

17:05.067 --> 17:06.808
Two million Tutsis murdered,

17:06.851 --> 17:09.419
hacked to death
by their neighbors.

17:09.463 --> 17:11.595
Two million!

17:11.639 --> 17:15.469
COMEDIAN:
What is the difference between
a car and a hundred dead Tutsis?

17:15.512 --> 17:16.905
DISC JOCKEY [laughs]:
What?

17:16.948 --> 17:18.863
COMEDIAN:
I don't have a car in my garage.

17:18.907 --> 17:22.302
[laughter,
applause sound effect]

17:22.345 --> 17:25.087
COMEDIAN:
How many dead Tutsis does it
take to change a lightbulb?

17:25.131 --> 17:27.785
DISC JOCKEY:
Oh, no. How many?

17:27.829 --> 17:31.833
COMEDIAN:
It must not be 30 because
my basement is still dark.

17:31.876 --> 17:33.095
[laughter]

17:33.139 --> 17:35.184
["I'll Make Love to You"
playing]

17:35.228 --> 17:38.405
DISC JOCKEY:
And now more hits from America.

17:38.448 --> 17:41.016
Number three
on the Billboardcharts.

17:41.060 --> 17:44.237
Boyz II Men's
"I'll Make Love to You."[beeps]

17:44.280 --> 17:47.544
DAVID:
Sonia, you said
you heard a voice.

17:47.588 --> 17:50.939
That was the voice of revenge.

17:50.982 --> 17:53.159
Listen to God's voice.

17:53.202 --> 17:54.899
He's the voice of justice.

17:54.943 --> 17:56.423
[wind whispering]

17:56.466 --> 17:59.774
Lando, tell the truth.

17:59.817 --> 18:03.604
[fading]:
Admit what you've done
and plead for mercy.

18:03.647 --> 18:06.433
Sonia is merciful.

18:06.476 --> 18:10.045
She is a truly good person.

18:10.089 --> 18:13.266
LANDO:
I was under orders
from the government militia

18:13.309 --> 18:15.355
to work at the station.

18:15.398 --> 18:17.357
But I was just an engineer.

18:17.400 --> 18:18.662
Sonia,

18:18.706 --> 18:19.924
every night I go

18:19.968 --> 18:21.926
to bed, and I
hear the screams

18:21.970 --> 18:23.624
of the children
who were murdered.

18:23.667 --> 18:26.061
Every night![Sonia exhales]

18:26.105 --> 18:28.542
Let me help you with that.

18:28.585 --> 18:29.934
No!

18:29.978 --> 18:31.153
[Lando screaming]

18:31.197 --> 18:33.286
No!

18:33.329 --> 18:34.765
[yelling]

18:39.988 --> 18:41.511
JUDGE:
You may begin,
Mr. Cormier.

18:41.555 --> 18:43.165
Thank you for the recess,
Your Honor.

18:43.209 --> 18:45.211
Just a few questions.

18:45.254 --> 18:48.083
Detective Byrd, is it true
you're writing a book

18:48.127 --> 18:50.172
about the serial killer
Dwight Ferrell?

18:52.783 --> 18:53.915
[exhales]

18:53.958 --> 18:55.873
You're shaking your head,
Detective.

18:55.917 --> 18:57.527
Does that mean no?

18:59.007 --> 19:01.183
No, it doesn't.

19:01.227 --> 19:03.925
I understand why you
might be embarrassed.

19:03.968 --> 19:06.101
Are you writing a book?

19:06.145 --> 19:07.711
Yes.

19:07.755 --> 19:09.844
CORMIER:
And it would increase
the book's salability

19:09.887 --> 19:11.062
if the body count

19:11.106 --> 19:12.455
of the serial killer
was increased.

19:12.499 --> 19:14.022
Objection. Offensive

19:14.065 --> 19:15.023
and prejudicial.

19:15.066 --> 19:16.981
It's a post-conviction hearing,

19:17.025 --> 19:19.027
Counselor.
The only person to prejudice

19:19.070 --> 19:22.335
is me. I'd like to hear
the detective's answer.

19:22.378 --> 19:23.901
My guess is what would
improve the salability

19:23.945 --> 19:25.120
would be the truth.

19:25.164 --> 19:28.558
Yeah. That's how it works.

19:28.602 --> 19:30.212
EMA: Objection!A cheap shot, Counselor.

19:30.256 --> 19:31.474
Sustained.

19:31.518 --> 19:33.563
I will happily withdraw.
Nothing further.

19:33.607 --> 19:35.870
JUDGE:
You are excused, Detective.

19:39.961 --> 19:42.137
The elevated troponin and BNP

19:42.181 --> 19:44.226
was a sign that Laura's
heart was being overworked,

19:44.270 --> 19:48.143
and the EKG shows severe
mitral valve regurgitation.

19:48.187 --> 19:50.450
The valve isn't healing.
It's worse.

19:50.493 --> 19:53.627
Okay. Uh, so, okay.
So, what do... what do we do?

19:53.670 --> 19:57.065
I need to perform an emergency
cardiac catheterization.

19:57.108 --> 19:58.980
[exhales]
What is that?

19:59.023 --> 20:01.809
A guide wire is led up to the
heart valve from the groin.

20:01.852 --> 20:03.724
It gives a diagnostic view

20:03.767 --> 20:05.116
of what is going on

20:05.160 --> 20:06.466
and allows us to
repair the valve.

20:06.509 --> 20:08.032
Okay, I just...
I need to get my wife.

20:08.076 --> 20:09.338
I-I understand.

20:09.382 --> 20:11.906
But I need to prep her
for surgery right now.

20:12.950 --> 20:14.865
Now? I mean, right now?

20:14.909 --> 20:16.084
Why? Why right now?

20:16.127 --> 20:18.042
I'm sorry if I haven't
made myself clear.

20:18.086 --> 20:19.914
I was hoping
that the valve would heal.

20:19.957 --> 20:21.655
Now I'm certain that it won't.

20:21.698 --> 20:25.093
It's too dangerous
not to deal with this now.

20:28.314 --> 20:30.272
[line ringing]

20:30.316 --> 20:32.143
KRISTEN [recorded]:
Hi, this is Kristen Bouchard.

20:32.187 --> 20:33.971
If you leave your name
and number, I'll...

20:34.015 --> 20:35.103
[phone beeps]Okay.

20:35.146 --> 20:36.235
Okay. If you got to do it,

20:36.278 --> 20:37.584
you got to do it. Okay.Yeah.

20:37.627 --> 20:39.629
[whimpering and grunting]

20:44.068 --> 20:47.420
Oh, my God.
You're just going to cut me up

20:47.463 --> 20:49.900
piece by piece.DAVID:
Lando, wait.

20:49.944 --> 20:51.162
Sonia,

20:51.206 --> 20:52.120
you believe
in mercy, right?

20:52.163 --> 20:53.295
That wasmercy.

20:53.339 --> 20:56.385
[Lando gasps, grunts]

20:56.429 --> 20:58.909
[tape tearing]Remember,

20:58.953 --> 21:02.086
Jesus healed the ear
of the soldier.

21:02.130 --> 21:04.872
"Those who draw the sword
will die by the sword."

21:04.915 --> 21:07.135
Yes, but he also said,

21:07.178 --> 21:10.094
"Think not that I am come
to bring peace on Earth:

21:10.138 --> 21:12.183
"I came not to bring peace

21:12.227 --> 21:14.185
but a sword."[screams]

21:15.970 --> 21:17.928
This sword.

21:17.972 --> 21:19.930
I'll get the
first aid kit.

21:24.761 --> 21:26.763
[grunting softly]

21:28.287 --> 21:30.811
[door closes]

21:32.203 --> 21:33.727
[muffled footsteps]

21:33.770 --> 21:35.381
You have to find the key.

21:35.424 --> 21:37.078
Quick, unlock me.

21:37.121 --> 21:38.427
There's no time.
[groaning]

21:38.471 --> 21:40.603
Sh-She's not gonna
let you live either.

21:40.647 --> 21:42.562
She's going to
kill both of us.

21:42.605 --> 21:44.346
What are you doing?

21:44.390 --> 21:45.521
[grunting]

21:45.565 --> 21:47.567
[creaking]

21:49.133 --> 21:51.092
Help!

21:51.135 --> 21:53.181
Help us! We're trapped!

21:53.224 --> 21:54.269
Help!

21:54.313 --> 21:56.358
Help! We're trapped!

21:56.402 --> 21:59.187
Help us!

21:59.230 --> 22:00.754
Help!

22:00.797 --> 22:02.364
Please!

22:02.408 --> 22:04.932
[faintly]:
Help us!

22:04.975 --> 22:07.413
[faintly]:
Help!

22:07.456 --> 22:08.849
[horn honks]

22:08.892 --> 22:10.285
[siren whoops]

22:11.330 --> 22:13.332
[horns honking]

22:21.427 --> 22:23.211
And it was during
one of these sessions

22:23.254 --> 22:26.301
that Mr. LeRoux
physically attacked you?Yes.

22:26.345 --> 22:28.129
He leaped across the table,

22:28.172 --> 22:30.697
forced me to the ground
and strangled me.

22:30.740 --> 22:33.787
Multiple prison guards had
to pull him off.

22:33.830 --> 22:35.354
Thank you,
Doctor.

22:35.397 --> 22:37.181
[mouthing]

22:37.225 --> 22:40.576
Mrs. Bouchard, did my client
actually jump at you

22:40.620 --> 22:42.143
because you
taunted him?

22:42.186 --> 22:43.362
No.Really?

22:43.405 --> 22:44.667
You do remember
you're under oath, right?

22:44.711 --> 22:46.190
Doctor? Is it "Doctor"?

22:46.234 --> 22:48.367
Yes, "Doctor."

22:48.410 --> 22:49.977
And I do remember...

22:50.020 --> 22:51.370
[chuckles]
that I'm under oath.

22:51.413 --> 22:52.980
EMA:
Okay, did you

22:53.023 --> 22:55.983
not tell Mr. LeRoux that he
will never get out of prison?

22:58.377 --> 23:00.161
Do you need a moment,
Mrs. Bouchard?

23:01.467 --> 23:04.121
I did say those words

23:04.165 --> 23:05.601
but not at the moment

23:05.645 --> 23:07.647
when Mr. LeRoux attacked me.

23:07.690 --> 23:09.257
Well, good.

23:09.300 --> 23:11.215
That is a relief.

23:11.259 --> 23:13.522
And did you not taunt
Mr. LeRoux by saying to him--

23:13.566 --> 23:16.438
here it is-- "You are 48 years
old, and prisons have

23:16.482 --> 23:19.354
good health care, so you won't
get out till you are 100"?

23:19.398 --> 23:20.921
I did say that.

23:20.964 --> 23:22.357
But, again,

23:22.401 --> 23:24.315
not prior to Mr. LeRoux
attacking me.

23:24.359 --> 23:26.448
Do you usually taunt
your patients?

23:26.492 --> 23:28.450
Mr. LeRoux
was not a patient.

23:28.494 --> 23:31.714
And, also,
I had already... resigned

23:31.758 --> 23:33.324
from the case.Resigned or been fired?

23:33.368 --> 23:34.891
Objection.

23:34.935 --> 23:36.153
Help!Help!

23:36.197 --> 23:38.112
Please!Help!

23:38.155 --> 23:39.679
Help us!We're-we're bleeding!

23:39.722 --> 23:40.941
Please. Help![barking in distance]

23:40.984 --> 23:43.596
Shh. Wait.

23:43.639 --> 23:45.032
[barking]

23:46.729 --> 23:48.339
What's wrong, Joker?

23:48.383 --> 23:50.037
[barking]

23:50.080 --> 23:51.386
Help!

23:51.430 --> 23:52.343
Help!Help!

23:52.387 --> 23:53.344
Please!

23:53.388 --> 23:55.738
[barking][shouting in distance]

23:55.782 --> 23:57.261
All right, leave it.

23:57.305 --> 23:59.263
Leave it. Joker, come.

23:59.307 --> 24:01.657
[barking]

24:01.701 --> 24:03.920
[barking fades]

24:03.964 --> 24:05.356
No!

24:05.400 --> 24:06.923
Wait!

24:06.967 --> 24:09.752
Help us!

24:09.796 --> 24:12.320
[exhales]
I'm maimed for life.

24:12.363 --> 24:14.888
She-She's going
to kill me.

24:14.931 --> 24:17.020
Just-just tell her the truth.

24:17.064 --> 24:19.370
I am telling her the truth.

24:19.414 --> 24:21.982
I am just a comedian.

24:22.025 --> 24:23.244
I am not a soldier.

24:23.287 --> 24:24.419
Then tell her that.

24:24.463 --> 24:26.334
Explain that.

24:26.377 --> 24:28.423
She's struggling with herself.

24:28.467 --> 24:30.730
She...LORI: Hello?

24:30.773 --> 24:32.340
Wait.

24:32.383 --> 24:33.820
[collar jangling in distance]

24:33.863 --> 24:35.430
[barking]

24:35.474 --> 24:37.084
Help us!

24:37.127 --> 24:38.346
We're here!We're down here!

24:38.389 --> 24:40.435
We're here! Please!Help!

24:40.479 --> 24:41.392
[barking][shouting in distance]

24:41.436 --> 24:42.872
Hello?

24:42.916 --> 24:43.786
[door slams open]

24:43.830 --> 24:46.049
[panting]

24:46.093 --> 24:47.442
[barking in distance]

24:47.486 --> 24:49.488
LORI:
Hello?

24:49.531 --> 24:51.054
He-Hello?

24:52.491 --> 24:54.449
You shouldn't have done that.

24:54.493 --> 24:56.538
You are a man of God.

24:56.582 --> 24:58.888
You shouldn't want
anybody else in this.

24:58.932 --> 25:00.934
Shh.

25:02.326 --> 25:03.458
[doorbell rings][gasps]

25:03.502 --> 25:05.504
[breathing heavily]

25:09.899 --> 25:12.380
This is your responsibility!

25:12.423 --> 25:14.382
[grunting]

25:14.425 --> 25:16.558
[panting]

25:16.602 --> 25:17.951
[doorbell rings]

25:17.994 --> 25:20.170
[squeals]

25:20.214 --> 25:22.216
[breathing heavily]

25:23.739 --> 25:25.872
[groans softly]
Don't do anything.

25:32.574 --> 25:35.185
[exhales][doorbell rings]

25:39.668 --> 25:41.627
[grunting on TV]

25:41.670 --> 25:43.672
[screaming]

25:49.330 --> 25:51.332
[glass shattering on TV]

25:51.375 --> 25:52.551
[screaming on TV]

25:55.902 --> 25:57.164
May I help you?

25:57.207 --> 25:59.340
Is everything all right?
I heard screaming coming

25:59.383 --> 26:01.342
from your basement,
someone calling for help.[growling softly]

26:01.385 --> 26:02.735
Oh, I think you
must be mistaken.

26:02.778 --> 26:04.214
Actually,

26:04.258 --> 26:07.043
I can't leave
until I know everything's okay.

26:07.087 --> 26:08.567
Like, ethically.

26:08.610 --> 26:12.005
I really hate how New Yorkers
don't care about each other.

26:12.048 --> 26:13.615
[muffled screaming on TV]

26:13.659 --> 26:14.790
Help!

26:14.834 --> 26:16.966
Help!Shh!

26:17.010 --> 26:19.403
Shut up. You're gonna get
somebody else killed.

26:19.447 --> 26:20.709
So what?

26:20.753 --> 26:22.581
She's killing me!

26:22.624 --> 26:24.147
Help!

26:24.191 --> 26:27.150
Help! Help!

26:27.194 --> 26:29.196
[screaming on TV][muffled shouting]

26:31.415 --> 26:35.376
[grunting]

26:35.419 --> 26:37.204
I'm watching a horror movie.

26:37.247 --> 26:38.684
I think that's what you heard.

26:38.727 --> 26:41.687
I know what a horror movie
sounds like.

26:41.730 --> 26:45.038
And if you are not willing
to investigate the situation,

26:45.081 --> 26:46.648
then maybe the police will.

26:46.692 --> 26:48.519
[exhales]

26:48.563 --> 26:50.304
I'm sorry.
[inhales]

26:50.347 --> 26:52.045
I recognize

26:52.088 --> 26:53.046
I'm being
a little cagey.

26:53.089 --> 26:54.830
I'm just, uh,

26:54.874 --> 26:56.440
embarrassed, is all.
[chuckles]

26:56.484 --> 26:58.617
My husband and I,

26:58.660 --> 26:59.922
we are in the middle
of, um,

26:59.966 --> 27:01.663
a bit of role-play.

27:01.707 --> 27:03.012
[chuckles]

27:03.056 --> 27:05.449
We've been going
through a dry spell,

27:05.493 --> 27:09.018
and, uh, I thought
the situation was hopeless,

27:09.062 --> 27:10.977
until we started exploring

27:11.020 --> 27:12.848
and...I'm sorry.
[chuckles]

27:12.892 --> 27:14.850
I feel like an idiot.

27:14.894 --> 27:16.504
[chuckles]

27:16.547 --> 27:19.681
Um, ha-have you tried
the Pleasure Palace on Wyeth?

27:19.725 --> 27:21.596
They have
some really great stuff there.

27:21.640 --> 27:22.771
SONIA:
Good idea.

27:22.815 --> 27:23.772
I will.

27:23.816 --> 27:25.034
Now, if you'll excuse me,

27:25.078 --> 27:27.210
he's in a very...
compromised position.

27:27.254 --> 27:28.647
[chuckles]
Got it.

27:28.690 --> 27:29.996
[both chuckle]

27:30.039 --> 27:31.780
[growling]

27:33.347 --> 27:34.696
[barking]Oh.
Oh. Hey.

27:34.740 --> 27:36.176
[laughs]
All right.

27:36.219 --> 27:37.177
Hey there.

27:37.220 --> 27:38.874
Sonia, right?[gasps]

27:38.918 --> 27:40.484
I'm Ben. I'm here for David.

27:40.528 --> 27:42.573
Ah. Right.

27:42.617 --> 27:44.532
[chuckles softly]
Come on in.

27:44.575 --> 27:46.795
Yeah.David is just, uh, out back.

27:46.839 --> 27:49.580
Such a pretty day.[phone vibrating]

27:49.624 --> 27:51.495
[groans]
Um...

27:51.539 --> 27:54.281
I-I'm sorry.
Just-just one second.

27:54.324 --> 27:56.849
Yeah. Hello?ANDY: Uh, hey, is this Ben?

27:56.892 --> 27:58.720
Yeah, who's this?This is Andy,

27:58.764 --> 28:00.156
Kristen's husband.Oh, hi.

28:00.200 --> 28:01.723
Hey.

28:01.767 --> 28:03.899
Uh, listen, I'm-I'm trying
to get in touch with Kristen,

28:03.943 --> 28:05.248
uh, but I can't.

28:05.292 --> 28:08.338
Um... is she with you?

28:08.382 --> 28:09.905
With me? No.

28:11.777 --> 28:14.257
[quietly]:
Look, it's-it's okay if she is.

28:14.301 --> 28:16.520
I just need her to know
that Laura is in the hospital

28:16.564 --> 28:18.174
for an emergency procedure.

28:18.218 --> 28:20.394
Oh, my God. I'm
so-- I'm so sorry.

28:20.437 --> 28:23.702
Uh, uh, I think she's
in, uh, court today.

28:23.745 --> 28:25.616
Well, she's not answering
my calls. I mean,

28:25.660 --> 28:27.618
uh, c-could you try her or...

28:27.662 --> 28:30.230
I just need her to get here.
Oxwell Hospital.

28:30.273 --> 28:31.361
Well, if she's not
answering your calls,

28:31.405 --> 28:32.493
she's probably not
gonna answer mi--

28:32.536 --> 28:34.974
O-Okay, le-let me-- let me try.

28:35.017 --> 28:36.584
I-I'm so sorry.
Just a minute.

28:36.627 --> 28:37.759
Take your time.

28:37.803 --> 28:39.761
Would you like a cup of tea?

28:39.805 --> 28:42.808
What? No, no, no,
thanks. Yeah.

28:42.851 --> 28:45.680
[line ringing]Come on, come on,
come on, come on.

28:45.724 --> 28:47.726
KRISTEN [recorded]:
Hi, this is Kristen Bouchard.[groans]

28:50.119 --> 28:52.818
Yeah, I can't, uh,
get her either.

28:52.861 --> 28:54.820
I think, uh, her cell
is probably off.

28:54.863 --> 28:58.649
Uh, look, I can head down to
the courthouse and tell her.

28:58.693 --> 29:00.260
You sure?Yes, definitely.

29:00.303 --> 29:02.697
Okay, just tell her that the
operation's going on right now.

29:02.741 --> 29:04.438
Wow. Okay. Uh, got it.

29:04.481 --> 29:05.787
Uh, we'll-we'll talk later.

29:05.831 --> 29:07.354
Uh, I'm so sorry.

29:07.397 --> 29:09.617
Please tell David that
I'll be back in about an hour.

29:09.660 --> 29:11.706
Uh, there's been a bit
of an emergency.

29:11.750 --> 29:14.056
Certainly.
Uh, I hope it all works out.

29:14.100 --> 29:16.145
Yeah. Me, too.

29:22.673 --> 29:24.240
[static]

29:30.899 --> 29:32.509
Hey. Here we are,

29:32.553 --> 29:34.424
just the two of us,
coming full circle.

29:34.468 --> 29:35.686
Oh, my goodness.

29:35.730 --> 29:38.515
Your testimony went
poorly today, didn't it?

29:38.559 --> 29:42.084
I think the judge was
leaning againstLeRoux

29:42.128 --> 29:43.520
until you testified.

29:43.564 --> 29:44.913
What do you think?

29:44.957 --> 29:46.480
And the sad thing is

29:46.523 --> 29:49.875
you had so many chances
to not get involved.

29:49.918 --> 29:52.747
How many times did I tell you
to go home to your daughters?

29:52.791 --> 29:55.141
Don't get involved in David.

29:55.184 --> 29:57.360
But then, every step of the way,

29:57.404 --> 29:59.362
you did the opposite.

29:59.406 --> 30:01.756
And now your husband's
offering this gift:

30:01.800 --> 30:03.497
go climbing.

30:03.540 --> 30:06.717
And, yet, here
you still are.

30:07.893 --> 30:12.462
I'm gonna do for you
what God did for Job.

30:12.506 --> 30:14.725
Job had only three daughters.

30:14.769 --> 30:16.379
God killed them.

30:16.423 --> 30:18.468
You have four daughters.

30:18.512 --> 30:20.949
I'm gonna kill every last one,

30:20.993 --> 30:22.037
then your husband,

30:22.081 --> 30:23.473
then burn down your house.

30:23.517 --> 30:25.084
I'm not gonna touch you though,

30:25.127 --> 30:27.086
no, because I want you
to live with the realization

30:27.129 --> 30:29.175
that you're responsible
for their deaths,

30:29.218 --> 30:31.090
that you let them die

30:31.133 --> 30:33.875
through your obstinacy,
your need

30:33.919 --> 30:37.487
to win...God, you talk too much.

30:39.098 --> 30:41.491
If I were you,
I would not...

30:41.535 --> 30:42.928
What, tempt you?

30:42.971 --> 30:44.712
Seriously?
Is that how the Devil works,

30:44.755 --> 30:46.888
he needs to be tempted
to do wrong?

30:46.932 --> 30:49.586
I am not to be trifled...

30:49.630 --> 30:51.545
Jake Perry.

30:53.416 --> 30:54.374
What?

30:54.417 --> 30:55.592
That's your real name.

30:55.636 --> 30:57.812
You're an insurance adjuster
from Des Moines.

31:00.423 --> 31:02.295
Or at least you were
until your second divorce.

31:02.338 --> 31:04.558
Then you moved to New York,
went to college and decided

31:04.601 --> 31:06.821
to recreate yourself
as Leland Townsend,

31:06.865 --> 31:08.954
a forensic psychologist
psychopath.

31:08.997 --> 31:10.390
Is that what
the Devil does?

31:10.433 --> 31:12.827
Uh, you...Yep, the Devil
may be tech-savvy,

31:12.871 --> 31:13.959
but so are we mortals.

31:14.002 --> 31:15.743
And all I had to do

31:15.786 --> 31:18.398
was use some of the genetic
material that you left

31:18.441 --> 31:21.227
on a glass in my kitchen, ask
the help of a detective friend

31:21.270 --> 31:23.620
and, bang,
there it was, a match.

31:23.664 --> 31:24.708
The Devil can use anybody...

31:24.752 --> 31:26.536
Really, Jake?

31:26.580 --> 31:28.060
"Jake the Flake,"

31:28.103 --> 31:31.672
shyest boy in the class of 1979
at Roosevelt High School.

31:31.715 --> 31:33.674
Honorary member
of band club.

31:33.717 --> 31:36.720
How was playing the tuba
in marching band?

31:36.764 --> 31:38.548
And let's talk
about your first wife.

31:38.592 --> 31:40.246
Aw. Janey.

31:40.289 --> 31:41.508
She wanted to have children,

31:41.551 --> 31:43.858
but you had trouble
getting it up, didn't you?

31:43.902 --> 31:45.294
None of this is true.

31:45.338 --> 31:46.730
And then
your second wife, Tina--

31:46.774 --> 31:48.428
she married you
for the money.

31:48.471 --> 31:50.343
Do you want to know how I know?

31:50.386 --> 31:51.910
I just gave her a call.

31:51.953 --> 31:56.088
I mean, you'd think if-if the
Devil had anybody to inhabit,

31:56.131 --> 31:58.525
he'd use a better specimen.

31:58.568 --> 32:00.701
No?

32:00.744 --> 32:02.703
I am going to...

32:02.746 --> 32:04.183
What? Hurt me?

32:04.226 --> 32:05.575
How?

32:05.619 --> 32:07.186
You're a nothing man
from Des Moines

32:07.229 --> 32:08.970
who is using the imagery
of satanism--

32:09.014 --> 32:10.711
a satanism you probably
don't even believe--

32:10.754 --> 32:12.713
to pretend you weren't
the third chair tuba player

32:12.756 --> 32:14.541
in the Roosevelt
High School band.

32:14.584 --> 32:16.760
Here's a thought... Jake.

32:16.804 --> 32:18.806
Get a life.

32:26.248 --> 32:28.250
Kristen!

32:28.294 --> 32:29.469
DAVID:
You're making a mistake!No, don't do it. Please!

32:29.512 --> 32:31.210
DAVID:
Don't do it, Sonia.I am only...

32:31.253 --> 32:34.082
This is wrong....asking if you are
right-handed.

32:34.126 --> 32:35.954
No. No, no, no, no, no!
I'm left-handed.

32:39.566 --> 32:42.134
Then this is the hand
that held the machete.

32:42.177 --> 32:43.700
[gasps]Lando, tell her!

32:44.571 --> 32:47.704
Just... tell her.

32:47.748 --> 32:49.750
[panting]

32:50.881 --> 32:53.014
I did not use a machete.

32:53.058 --> 32:56.365
I did not!Just... what did you do?

32:58.759 --> 33:00.717
I was funny.

33:00.761 --> 33:03.329
That's all.

33:03.372 --> 33:05.374
I-I said what I was told to say.

33:05.418 --> 33:07.637
And you said those things?!

33:07.681 --> 33:10.640
Yes! Yes!
[panting]

33:10.684 --> 33:12.642
I never hurt anyone.

33:12.686 --> 33:16.037
I'm a comedian.
I make jokes.

33:16.081 --> 33:18.474
I-I love Robin Williams.

33:18.518 --> 33:20.433
I love Richard Pryor.

33:20.476 --> 33:22.522
I-I punch up.
I don't punch down.

33:22.565 --> 33:24.089
Punch up at what?!

33:24.132 --> 33:26.134
Tutsis.

33:27.440 --> 33:29.398
They were wealthy.

33:29.442 --> 33:31.400
They-they had power.

33:31.444 --> 33:32.662
They had cattle.

33:32.706 --> 33:34.795
I told jokes about them.

33:34.838 --> 33:37.319
Every comedian
makes fun of people,

33:37.363 --> 33:40.018
but you make fun
of people in power.

33:41.497 --> 33:42.629
[gasps sharply]

33:42.672 --> 33:45.545
It doesn't make
people into killers.

33:48.548 --> 33:51.681
That was a confession, Sonia.

33:53.509 --> 33:55.511
Let him go.

33:55.555 --> 33:57.557
Please.

34:01.517 --> 34:02.823
DAUGHTERS:
...nir-yatayami.

34:02.866 --> 34:05.086
Idam guru ratna
mandala-kam

34:05.130 --> 34:08.133
nir-yatayami.
Idam guru ratna...

34:08.176 --> 34:10.222
Kristen?

34:10.265 --> 34:12.137
Idam guru... Is Laura okay?

34:12.180 --> 34:13.442
She's fine.
She's fine.Where is she?

34:13.486 --> 34:14.661
She's in the recovery room.

34:14.704 --> 34:16.619
Ben, the Magnificent!

34:16.663 --> 34:18.534
They're operating on Laura.Hey. Hey. Aw.

34:18.578 --> 34:20.841
Come here. We're
gonna make...

34:20.884 --> 34:22.582
Hey. Oh.

34:22.625 --> 34:24.627
What were they doing?

34:24.671 --> 34:26.499
I-I don't know.
I didn't see.

34:26.542 --> 34:28.501
They were chanting.Were they?

34:28.544 --> 34:30.677
Yeah.Is-is that a problem
if they were?

34:30.720 --> 34:32.331
I just think we should discuss

34:32.374 --> 34:34.942
before sharing any
religion with the girls.

34:34.985 --> 34:36.813
I didn't share anything
with them.

34:36.857 --> 34:39.077
Well, then
how did they...?Oh, I don't know.

34:39.120 --> 34:41.166
How do they find out anything?
The Internet.

34:42.950 --> 34:46.954
I was in the church when I heard
the... the gates torn open.

34:46.997 --> 34:51.611
I ran, but I was struck
from behind with a metal pipe.

34:51.654 --> 34:54.048
I fell.

34:54.092 --> 34:56.659
And my sister fell next to me.

34:56.703 --> 34:58.792
Half her face was gone.

34:58.835 --> 35:00.968
I pretended to be dead.

35:01.011 --> 35:02.404
Even as I heard

35:02.448 --> 35:05.059
the Hutus take the babies

35:05.103 --> 35:07.105
from the arms of their mothers

35:07.148 --> 35:09.281
and crack their heads

35:09.324 --> 35:11.718
on the western
wall of the church.

35:11.761 --> 35:14.199
Oh, there were so many...

35:14.242 --> 35:17.158
terrible things I heard.

35:17.202 --> 35:21.336
But the most terrible sound
was the laughing.

35:21.380 --> 35:23.512
The Hutu men

35:23.556 --> 35:25.514
telling your jokes

35:25.558 --> 35:28.517
about cockroaches
and laughing

35:28.561 --> 35:31.781
as they hacked everyone
to pieces.

35:31.825 --> 35:33.827
[cries]

35:35.655 --> 35:37.700
[wind whispering]

35:39.615 --> 35:41.965
[whispering continues]

35:46.361 --> 35:48.494
Sonia.

35:59.592 --> 36:01.681
I believe God sees everything.

36:03.030 --> 36:06.947
He will understand
why I do what I do.

36:06.990 --> 36:09.036
No! No!

36:09.079 --> 36:11.473
I'm sorry!
I'm sorry. I'm so sor...

36:11.517 --> 36:13.823
I'm just very sorry.

36:13.867 --> 36:15.869
Believe me.

36:16.870 --> 36:18.698
[sighs]

36:20.917 --> 36:22.963
[sighs heavily]

36:23.006 --> 36:24.965
Thank you.

36:25.008 --> 36:26.619
I forgive you.

36:26.662 --> 36:28.708
Your soul is clean.

36:28.751 --> 36:30.753
Ah. [panting]

36:36.672 --> 36:39.240
[gasps]

36:48.989 --> 36:50.686
Why did you do that?

36:50.730 --> 36:52.253
He asked forgiveness.

36:52.297 --> 36:53.950
And I forgave him.

36:53.994 --> 36:56.475
But you killed him.

36:56.518 --> 36:58.259
Yes.

36:58.303 --> 37:00.261
But not for revenge.

37:00.305 --> 37:02.437
For justice.

37:02.481 --> 37:04.265
[phone dialing]

37:04.309 --> 37:06.180
Hello.

37:06.224 --> 37:10.271
There has been a shooting
at 1865 Grand.

37:10.315 --> 37:12.578
Yes, one dead body.

37:12.621 --> 37:15.929
Sonia Kamanzi.

37:15.972 --> 37:18.279
I shot him.

37:19.324 --> 37:20.890
Yes.

37:23.197 --> 37:25.155
And please send an ambulance.

37:25.199 --> 37:27.419
There's an injured man
here, too.

37:47.134 --> 37:49.267
JUDGE:
The question is always
about justice.

37:49.310 --> 37:52.444
How best to servejustice.

37:52.487 --> 37:55.708
These murders may have
at first appeared

37:55.751 --> 37:57.884
to be two separate cases,

37:57.927 --> 38:01.104
but after careful
consideration,

38:01.148 --> 38:02.454
there is only one.

38:02.497 --> 38:04.238
Orson LeRoux,

38:04.282 --> 38:06.022
I overturn your conviction
on all counts.

38:06.066 --> 38:07.633
You are free to go.[gallery clamoring]

38:07.676 --> 38:08.590
Your Honor!

38:08.634 --> 38:11.898
I have ruled,Mr. D.A.

38:15.597 --> 38:18.600
He's gonna kill me.
He's gonna kill me.

38:18.644 --> 38:20.907
He's gonna kill me. He's
gonna kill me.

38:20.950 --> 38:22.212
May I hug you, sir?

38:24.214 --> 38:26.956
I want you to have this.

38:27.000 --> 38:28.828
It's my personal Bible.

38:28.871 --> 38:32.962
I hope it helps you
find some peace.

38:33.006 --> 38:34.486
I was so brave.

38:34.529 --> 38:37.967
You really were, and
I'm so proud of you.

38:38.011 --> 38:39.186
LAURA:
It's over.

38:39.229 --> 38:40.666
LYNN:
Are you all better?

38:40.709 --> 38:42.929
LAURA:
Yeah, a little bit.
It still hurts there.

38:42.972 --> 38:44.626
Can I see your scar?Yeah.

38:44.670 --> 38:46.149
It's underneath.

38:46.193 --> 38:47.542
They're gonna
bandage around it.

38:47.586 --> 38:48.891
LILA:
Did they put
you to sleep?

38:48.935 --> 38:50.502
LAURA: Yeah.Did the medicine
taste good?

38:50.545 --> 38:51.851
LAURA:
No.

38:51.894 --> 38:53.592
Doctor gave it to me,
but I didn't like it.

38:53.635 --> 38:54.897
LEXIS:
No medicine tastes good.

38:54.941 --> 38:56.246
Doctor, is Laura
gonna be all right?

38:56.290 --> 38:57.596
Oh, the doctor.Hi, Doctor.

38:57.639 --> 38:59.249
[clamoring]Can I see a picture
of the heart?

38:59.293 --> 39:00.816
Guys, guys, guys, guys, guys.Like, I really
wanted to hold it.

39:00.860 --> 39:02.818
Shh, shh.
We need to talk to the doctor.

39:02.862 --> 39:04.646
Okay, Mommy.

39:09.477 --> 39:11.436
Is everything okay?

39:11.479 --> 39:12.741
[sighs]

39:12.785 --> 39:14.961
The results are a bit unusual.

39:15.004 --> 39:16.571
Okay.

39:16.615 --> 39:19.531
Sometime between the EKG and
performing the cardiac cath...

39:19.574 --> 39:20.706
Mm-hmm.

39:20.749 --> 39:22.708
...the mitral valve
in Laura's heart

39:22.751 --> 39:24.753
has completely healed.

39:25.798 --> 39:27.452
It has?

39:27.495 --> 39:30.368
Yes. And I don't know how.

39:30.411 --> 39:32.805
Young bodies
are mysterious to us.

39:32.848 --> 39:36.504
Sometimes they heal
unexpectedly, sometimes

39:36.548 --> 39:39.594
even... miraculously.

39:42.684 --> 39:46.340
DAUGHTERS:
Idam guru ratna
mandala-kam nir-yatayami.

39:46.384 --> 39:50.605
Idam guru ratna mandala-kam
nir-yatayami.

39:53.608 --> 39:55.567
I've made a choice.

39:55.610 --> 39:56.829
Oh, yeah?

39:56.872 --> 39:58.439
Yeah.

39:58.483 --> 39:59.658
Tell me.

39:59.701 --> 40:01.224
[sighs]

40:01.268 --> 40:03.226
I'm gonna stay.

40:03.270 --> 40:04.663
You go to Denver.

40:04.706 --> 40:06.926
No. It's your turn.

40:06.969 --> 40:08.449
Laura's well.
The kids are great.

40:08.493 --> 40:09.885
I can take care of them.

40:09.929 --> 40:12.192
I know you can, but I'm-I'm
not doing it for you.

40:12.235 --> 40:13.976
I'm doing it for me.

40:14.020 --> 40:17.153
I have a career here--
something that's challenging me.

40:17.197 --> 40:19.808
I... I don't want
to give it up.

40:22.811 --> 40:24.813
Okay. Okay.

40:25.814 --> 40:27.599
I'll go to Denver
to set it up,

40:27.642 --> 40:30.340
but I'm gonna get
one of the boys to run it.

40:30.384 --> 40:32.255
You don't have to.

40:32.299 --> 40:33.996
I know.

40:34.040 --> 40:36.042
Okay.

40:43.223 --> 40:47.009
So, um...

40:47.053 --> 40:48.533
the chant.

40:48.576 --> 40:50.143
Mm.

40:50.186 --> 40:52.624
What does it mean?
What were you praying for?

40:52.667 --> 40:54.756
Tong-Lin.
It-it means "giving and taking."

40:54.800 --> 40:56.845
It's like an exchange.

40:57.846 --> 40:59.848
What were you exchanging?

41:01.546 --> 41:03.504
Uh... well, I...

41:03.548 --> 41:06.942
I asked for Laura
to be healed.

41:06.986 --> 41:10.076
Um... in exchange
for my life.

41:11.120 --> 41:12.687
Andy.

41:12.731 --> 41:15.516
No. Don't worry.
It's just a mantra.

41:15.560 --> 41:17.866
Come on. Hey.

41:23.393 --> 41:25.526
LELAND:
She has this way
of getting to me.

41:25.570 --> 41:28.660
I'll be feeling all-knowing
and all-powerful, and then,

41:28.703 --> 41:32.664
she's in my face,
and I just feel... impotent.

41:32.707 --> 41:34.666
When you say
"impotent,"

41:34.709 --> 41:36.755
do you mean
sexually?

41:36.798 --> 41:38.452
No. Uh...

41:38.496 --> 41:41.281
She's talking about Jake
the Flake and the marching band.

41:41.324 --> 41:44.066
And why do people make fun
of marching bands?!

41:44.110 --> 41:45.677
That's a worthy entertainment.

41:45.720 --> 41:47.548
And I just...

41:47.592 --> 41:49.550
[sighs]

41:49.594 --> 41:51.683
I should have ripped out
her heart.

41:51.726 --> 41:54.337
Why didn't you?

41:54.381 --> 41:57.515
It's not part of the plan,
or has that changed?

41:59.734 --> 42:01.954
Do you wantthe
plan to change?

42:04.609 --> 42:06.567
No.

42:06.611 --> 42:08.700
Good.

42:08.743 --> 42:11.180
Then find someone else
to take her heart out,

42:11.224 --> 42:14.488
and you and I will
eat it together.

42:14.532 --> 42:17.491
Now tell me
about your dreams.

